==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hoa
<hw>Hoa</hw> }</mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[See <er>Ho</er>, <pos>interj.</pos>, 2.]</ety> <def>A stop; a
halt; a moderation of pace.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There is no <qex>ho</qex> with them.</q>
<rj><qau>Decker.</qau></rj></p>

<p><ent>Ho</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Hoa
<hw>Hoa</hw> }</mhw> <pr>(h⟦omac⟧)</pr>,
<pos>interj.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F. & G. <ets>ho</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Halloo! attend! -- a call to excite attention, or to give notice of
approach.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧What noise there, <xex>ho</xex>?⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj> ⟦ldquo⟧<qex>Ho</qex>! who's within?⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Shak.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <ety>[Perhaps corrupted fr. <ets>hold</ets>; but cf. F.
<ets>hau</ets> stop! and E. <ets>whoa</ets>.]</ety> <def>Stop! stand
still! hold! -- a word now used by teamsters, but formerly to order the
cessation of anything.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>whoa</asp>, and,
formerly, <asp>hoo</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The duke . . . pulled out his sword and cried
⟦ldquo⟧<qex>Hoo</qex>!⟦rdquo⟧</q> <rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An herald on a scaffold made an <qex>hoo</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>hoactzin</ent>⟦br⟧
